Jenkins Security (Authorization):
---------------------------------
    Manage jenkins --> config global -> security

    Security Concepts:
    ------------------
    security realm: jenkins own database (default)
    LDAP: (realtime usage)

    authorization strategies:
    --------------------------
    Logged-in users: Full access (Not recommended)
    Matrix-based: Fine-grained control
    Project-based matrix: job-level access
    Role-based: recommended for real-time

    install role-based plugin:
    --------------------------
    manage jenkins --> manage plugins --> install --> Role-Based Authorization Strategy

    Matrix-Based Authorization:
    ---------------------------
        Steps:
            select - project-based matrix authorization
            add user
            assign permissions

        Permissions Types:
            overall:
                admin
                read

            job:
                build
                configure
                delete
                create

            view:
                create/delete/read

        Example:
        --------
        User: Admin (Full)
        Developer: Read only
        Devops: Build + Configure

        * if user is not added -- cannot login (even if valid user)

    Project-Level Security:
    ------------------------
    Requirement: user sees only specific jobs
        steps:
            go to job -config
            enable: project-based security
            add user
            assign permissions

        example:
        --------
            Mithun  Facebook jobs only
            Rithvik Maven jobs only







































